                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <p>Elegant early Hellenistic lettering: sigma has mildly diverging outer strokes, mu
                                    more evidently so; theta and omicron are consistently smaller than
                                    other letters and placed above the base line; pi has a projecting
                                    upper horizontal and short right descender; the branches of upsilon
                                    are straight; letter strokes are finished with small
                                    serifs.</p>
